==English==

===Pronunciation===

===Etymology===
English; '''[[office]]''' + ''suffix'' '''[[-er]]'''

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# One who has a position of [[authority]] in a [[hierarchy|hierarchical]] [[organization]], especially in [[military]], [[police]] or [[government]] organizations.
# One who holds a [[public]] office.
# An [[agent]] or [[servant]] [[impart]]ed with the [[ability]], to some degree, to act on [[initiative]].
# ''(colloquial, military)'' A simple contraction of the term "[[commission]]ed officer."

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}}: To [[supply]] with '''officers'''.
# {{transitive}}: To [[command]] like an '''officer'''.

